        "comment_author": "sigabrtv1-ui",
        "comment_body": "@saiarcot895 @qiluo-msft Hi, on behalf of Dawei Huang \u2014 we have an active trixie migration effort for gnmi containers that is blocked on this PR.\n\n**Tracking issue:** sonic-net/sonic-buildimage#25959\n**Related PRs:**\n- sonic-net/sonic-buildimage#25957 \u2014 migrate gnmi/telemetry/watchdog containers to Trixie (KVM FIPS test failing)\n- sonic-net/sonic-gnmi#611 \u2014 bump go directive for Trixie compatibility\n- sonic-net/sonic-mgmt-common#208 \u2014 bump go.mod to 1.21 for Trixie\n\nThe KVM FIPS test (`fips/test_fips.py`) is failing because the telemetry binary (Go) is not loading `libsymcrypt.so` \u2014 the root cause is that sonic-fips still provides Go 1.19 while the trixie build environment uses Go 1.24, so the telemetry binary gets compiled with the non-FIPS system Go and has no SymCrypt integration.\n\nThis PR (#78) bumping FIPS Go to 1.24 is exactly what we need. Could we get this reviewed and merged? Thanks!"
    },
